value.0: Low and flat, this chest seems to have been designed for the storage and filing of a merchant's accounts.
Metal studs poke through the woodwork of this ornate chest. Judging by the fine craftsmanship, this footlocker appears to have been intended for public display.
Strange runes and pictographs, likely arcane in nature, have been scorched into the sides of this hide-covered strongbox.
The wood's rich grain adds an unexpected vibrancy to this humble cabinet. Whoever crafted it clearly did so with great love.
A small chest for storing valuables.
